<taxonomicName id="D6344FBFC243A055D632513164C771CB" authorityName="P. H. Hoekstra" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis komorensis" order="Magnoliales" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="komorensis">
<emphasis id="18CE91A8F70EEE5235DF9C008C3F5D65" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Monanthotaxis komorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(green circles) on the Comoros archipelago.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B3C28C2FF611979C65365AF84D4B7D0C" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="52086044EECC11190682DB73F97B1952" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="80032DE84DF5AB4529055A00607E3290" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Steep escarpment with dense thicket, stony-gravelly soil at 700 m altitude.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8F0DB7C2DCD1BD9D589A94C89B77121D" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="8AC43A75A08A513054C50DD5A2C44DC9" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A7A31EE8B5930F94A96AB46D0BE18EC3" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Flowers collected the 7th of February.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2AA9CD57B1A152A641F884A5822CEB94" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="F0CF06EA5F68F90596C5D5ABBBBA9CBD" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="21335AF2453884577CB5F25FED8C889D" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">
Proposed IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis id="413323FE8E17CFB8CF7FA3280CD340A8" bold="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Critically Endangered</emphasis>
(CR): B2ab(ii, iii), only known from one collection in the Rondo Forest Reserve in South-east Tanzania. Although it occurs in a forest reserve, satellite images provided by Google Earth (assessed May 2016) show that a major part of the forest in the reserve systematically has been removed, and forest cover is declining over the years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D5DFF8609B0D5DE92727833F7D268F28" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA8AA0EAB89FD817896F56BF25BEA1F6" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D84877EF32D3D76090631A414A2F33F6" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">
From the latin 
<emphasis id="B6B589C3481B7C5ACF462FD6ED2AD441" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">fili</emphasis>
, thread-like, and 
<emphasis id="724FEF5F4A0EA9545775E094F63A8F3D" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">pes</emphasis>
, foot/stalk; referring to the filiform pedicels.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="813CA2DA90D1ED081F1A6525CD9DCB25" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="53477CCCC48E4CFEB3B1CAF6A3881EAB" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">
<pageBreakToken id="C66520E9666327D212C356F4229945B9" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" start="start">Discussion</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D255F507097591BBB537A0CDF371D8A" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">
This species is vegetatively very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DCB2B853D79D189EC1561AAEBE605FF1" authorityName="Verdcourt" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Diels" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis trichantha" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="60BEF7695C1EA1B80AF106C5701EBE93" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis trichantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which also occurs in South-East Tanzania. The flowers and inflorescences are very different with 
<taxonomicName id="4C7ACBF729AFA7C4222F4A3CBE145C58" authorityName="P. H. Hoekstra" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis filipes" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filipes">
<emphasis id="D5B10EEEB2AD17CD8BDBE8F7ED1DA72C" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis filipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having pending flowers on long pedicels and the inflorescences supra-axillary, while 
<taxonomicName id="EF33082620776062B5975C00A232CFC7" authorityName="Verdcourt" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Diels" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis trichantha" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trichantha">
<emphasis id="B877646AF1EC1DD0248EEC287AE6213B" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis trichantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short pedicels which are extra-axillary or leaf-opposed (table 2). Apart from 
<taxonomicName id="EE43B5927A2A94344AB267CF3D1F5C72" authorityName="P. H. Hoekstra" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis filipes" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="filipes">
<emphasis id="191F4F99A6D8B944C49ECC8E329B0C24" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis filipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, long filiform pedicels only occur in some species of 
<taxonomicName id="B919CB756703291B2AC32BDB23B91ED7" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BC59A3F64137C5C2E28F67C87597C11D" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Madagascar (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="F96B9CCB8FE0291106ED1F8EABCC2EE7" authorityName="Verdcourt" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Diels" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis caesia" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caesia">
<emphasis id="7652D6957B25DB2057A03F646C4D71E1" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis caesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Diels) Verdc. and 
<taxonomicName id="791C963685F91C434854D959DB285A8B" authorityName="Verdcourt" authorityYear="1971" baseAuthorityName="Baill." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis heterantha" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterantha">
<emphasis id="44DE491D78F55EDD626C63015112AA59" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis heterantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Baill.) Verdc. These species lack the dense indumentum on the young twigs. Also 
<taxonomicName id="55AF1336C93E09CB388D1B0C97F5C512" authorityName="Exell" authorityYear="1932" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis oligandra" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligandra">
<emphasis id="E8F65930FDB2D80602399F3027624C78" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis oligandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Exell has pending supra-axillary inflorescences, but in this species the sympodial rachis (peduncle) is filiform instead of the pedicels, which are very short. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName id="1BCC90B2893D8099C296C4A1CE3D363F" authorityName="Exell" authorityYear="1932" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Monanthotaxis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Monanthotaxis oligandra" order="Magnoliales" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligandra">
<emphasis id="C4F6992C687964EDD5688556E1CA453D" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">Monanthotaxis oligandra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks the dense yellow pubescence and has very different flowers with all petals in a single whorl.
</paragraph>
